The makefile and program is intended to run on Linux

To compile the program, just run make.

The entirity of the ray tracer is contained in raytracer.cpp, which relies on CImg.h
If you want to run this on another system, just compile raytracer.cpp with the commands found here:
http://cimg.eu/reference/group__cimg__overview.html

You can then run the executable.

Test.cpp is a test program to ensure the correctness of CImg. 
It displays a 256 by 256 image with blue color increase on the x axis, and red color increasing on the y axis.